{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_27868e1435e54d3b9d74f560","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t==============\n2\tSphinx-Gallery\n3\t==============\n4\t\n5\t.. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/sphinx-gallery\n6\t    :target: https://pypi.org/project/sphinx-gallery/\n7\t    :alt: PyPI\n8\t\n9\t.. image:: https://img.shields.io/conda/vn/conda-forge/sphinx-gallery\n10\t    :target: https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/sphinx-gallery\n11\t    :alt: Conda-forge\n12\t\n13\t.. image:: https://zenodo.org/badge/DOI/10.5281/zenodo.3741780.svg\n14\t    :target: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741780\n15\t    :alt: Zenodo DOI\n16\t\n17\t.. image:: https://dev.azure.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery/_apis/build/status/sphinx-gallery.sphinx-gallery?branchName=master\n18\t    :target: https://dev.azure.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery/_build/latest?definitionId=1&branchName=master\n19\t    :alt: Azure CI status\n20\t\n21\t.. image:: https://circleci.com/gh/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery.svg?style=shield\n22\t    :target: https://circleci.com/gh/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery\n23\t    :alt: CircleCI status\n24\t\n25\t.. image:: https://codecov.io/github/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery/badge.svg?branch=master&service=github(\n26\t    :target: https://app.codecov.io/github/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery\n27\t    :alt: Code coverage\n28\t\n29\t\n30\t.. tagline-begin-content\n31\t\n32\tA `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/master/>`_ extension that builds an\n33\tHTML gallery of examples from any set of Python scripts.\n34\tCheck out the `documentation`_ for introductions on how to use it and more...\n35\t\n36\t.. tagline-end-content\n37\t\n38\t.. image:: doc/_static/demo.png\n39\t   :width: 80%\n40\t   :alt: A demo of a gallery generated by Sphinx-Gallery\n41\t\n42\tQuickstart\n43\t==========\n44\t\n45\tSphinx-Gallery can be used to generate an example gallery from ``.py`` files,\n46\tfor a library,\n47\tas well as a stand-alone web page showcasing examples of a particular\n48\tPython package, module, or class.\n49\t\n50\tLet's get started with a simple example or check out the\n51\t `documentation`_ for introductions on how\n52\t to use it and more...\n53\t\n54\tInstall via ``pip``\n55\t-------------------\n56\t\n57\t.. installation-begin-content\n58\t\n59\tYou can do a direct install via ``pip`` by using:\n60\t\n61\t.. code-block:: bash\n62\t\n63\t    $ pip install sphinx-gallery\n64\t\n65\t.. tip::\n66\t    Sphinx-Gallery also has support for scraping images from Matplotlib\n67\t    and Matplotlib-based packages such as Seaborn.\n68\t    We recommend installing system ``optipng`` binaries to reduce\n69\t    the file sizes of the generated PNG files.\n70\t\n71\t.. installation-end-content\n72\t\n73\tAdd examples to your docs\n74\t-------------------------\n75\t\n76\tLet's assume simple scenario, you have a Python package with a directory structure like this:\n77\t\n78\t.. code-block::\n79\t\n80\t    ├── doc\n81\t    │   ├── conf.py\n82\t    │   ├── index.rst\n83\t    |   ├── make.bat\n84\t    │   └── Makefile\n85\t    ├── my_python_module\n86\t    │   ├── __init__.py\n87\t    │   └── mod.py\n88\t    └── examples\n89\t        ├── plot_example.py\n90\t        └── README.txt (or .rst)\n91\t\n92\tEnable Sphinx-Gallery by adding the following to your ``doc/conf.py``:\n93\t\n94\t.. code-block:: python\n95\t\n96\t    extensions = [\n97\t        ...\n98\t        'sphinx_gallery.gen_gallery',\n99\t    ]\n100\t\n101\t    # path to the examples scripts\n102\t    sphinx_gallery_conf = {\n103\t        'examples_dirs': '../examples',   # path to your example scripts\n104\t        'gallery_dirs': 'auto_examples',  # path to where to save gallery generated output\n105\t    }\n106\t\n107\tFinally just compile your docs as usual.\n108\tSphinx-Gallery will generate reST files, adding execution outputs, and save them in ``auto_examples/``.\n109\tAdd a link to ``auto_examples/index.rst`` to include the gallery in your documentation.\n110\t\n111\tWho uses Sphinx-Gallery\n112\t=======================\n113\t\n114\tAn incomplete list:\n115\t\n116\t.. projects_list_start\n117\t\n118\t* `Apache TVM <https://tvm.apache.org/docs/tutorial/index.html>`_\n119\t* `Atomistic Cookbook <https://atomistic-cookbook.org>`_\n120\t* `auto-sklearn <https://automl.github.io/auto-sklearn/master/examples/index.html>`_\n121\t* `Biotite <https://www.biotite-python.org/latest/examples/index.html>`_\n122\t* `Cartopy <https://cartopy.readthedocs.io/stable/gallery/index.html>`_\n123\t* `FURY <https://fury.gl/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n124\t* `pyGIMLi <https://www.pygimli.org/_examples_auto/index.html>`_\n125\t* `HyperSpy <https://hyperspy.org/hyperspy-doc/current/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n126\t* `kikuchipy <https://kikuchipy.org/en/stable/examples/index.html>`_\n127\t* `Matplotlib <https://matplotlib.org/stable/gallery/index>`_\n128\t* `MNE-Python <https://mne.tools/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n129\t* `napari <https://napari.org/stable/gallery.html>`_\n130\t* `Nestle <http://kylebarbary.com/nestle/examples/index.html>`_\n131\t* `NetworkX <https://networkx.org/documentation/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n132\t* `Neuraxle <https://www.neuraxle.org/stable/examples/index.html>`_\n133\t* `Nilearn <https://nilearn.github.io/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n134\t* `OpenML <https://openml.github.io/openml-python/main/examples/index.html>`_\n135\t* `OpenTURNS <https://openturns.github.io/openturns/latest/examples/examples.html>`_\n136\t* `Optuna <https://optuna.readthedocs.io/en/stable/tutorial/index.html>`_\n137\t* `PlasmaPy <https://docs.plasmapy.org/en/latest/examples.html>`_\n138\t* `POT <https://pythonot.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n139\t* `PyGMT <https://www.pygmt.org/latest/gallery/index.html>`_\n140\t* `pyRiemann <https://pyriemann.readthedocs.io/en/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n141\t* `PyStruct <https://pystruct.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n142\t* `PySurfer <https://pysurfer.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n143\t* `PyTorch tutorials <https://pytorch.org/tutorials>`_\n144\t* `PyVista <https://docs.pyvista.org/examples/>`_\n145\t* `pyxem <https://www.pyxem.org/en/stable/examples/index.html>`_\n146\t* `RADIS <https://radis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n147\t* `scikit-image <https://scikit-image.org/docs/dev/auto_examples/>`_\n148\t* `scikit-learn <https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n149\t* `SimPEG <https://docs.simpeg.xyz/content/examples/>`_\n150\t* `SKADA Scikit-adaptation <https://scikit-adaptation.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n151\t* `Sphinx-Gallery <https://sphinx-gallery.github.io/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n152\t* `SunPy <https://docs.sunpy.org/en/stable/generated/gallery/index.html>`_\n153\t* `Tonic <https://tonic.readthedocs.io/en/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n154\t* `TorchDR <https://torchdr.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n155\t* `TorchIO <https://torchio.readthedocs.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n156\t\n157\t.. projects_list_end\n158\t\n159\tContributing\n160\t============\n161\t\n162\tYou can get the latest development source from our `Github repository\n163\t<https://github.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery>`_. You need\n164\t``setuptools`` installed in your system to install Sphinx-Gallery. For example,\n165\tyou can do:\n166\t\n167\t.. code-block:: console\n168\t\n169\t    $ git clone https://github.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery\n170\t    $ cd sphinx-gallery\n171\t    $ conda install graphviz  # if using conda, you can get graphviz this way\n172\t    $ pip install -e .[dev]\n173\t\n174\t\n175\tCheck that you are all set by running:\n176\t\n177\t.. code-block:: console\n178\t\n179\t    $ pytest sphinx_gallery\n180\t\n181\tHow to cite\n182\t===========\n183\t\n184\t.. citation-begin-content\n185\t\n186\tIf you would like to cite Sphinx-Gallery you can do so using our `Zenodo\n187\tdeposit <https://zenodo.org/record/3741780>`_.\n188\t\n189\t.. _documentation: https://sphinx-gallery.github.io/\n190\t\n191\t.. citation-end-content\n192\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"874ed280-4498-46b3-b8b6-405dcde56ae2","uuid":"e349ab67-03e3-4382-b93d-7bf72b239dd0","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:16:29.863Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.rst","content":"==============\nSphinx-Gallery\n==============\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/sphinx-gallery\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/sphinx-gallery/\n    :alt: PyPI\n\n.. image:: https://img.shields.io/conda/vn/conda-forge/sphinx-gallery\n    :target: https://anaconda.org/conda-forge/sphinx-gallery\n    :alt: Conda-forge\n\n.. image:: https://zenodo.org/badge/DOI/10.5281/zenodo.3741780.svg\n    :target: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741780\n    :alt: Zenodo DOI\n\n.. image:: https://dev.azure.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery/_apis/build/status/sphinx-gallery.sphinx-gallery?branchName=master\n    :target: https://dev.azure.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery/_build/latest?definitionId=1&branchName=master\n    :alt: Azure CI status\n\n.. image:: https://circleci.com/gh/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery.svg?style=shield\n    :target: https://circleci.com/gh/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery\n    :alt: CircleCI status\n\n.. image:: https://codecov.io/github/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery/badge.svg?branch=master&service=github(\n    :target: https://app.codecov.io/github/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery\n    :alt: Code coverage\n\n\n.. tagline-begin-content\n\nA `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/master/>`_ extension that builds an\nHTML gallery of examples from any set of Python scripts.\nCheck out the `documentation`_ for introductions on how to use it and more...\n\n.. tagline-end-content\n\n.. image:: doc/_static/demo.png\n   :width: 80%\n   :alt: A demo of a gallery generated by Sphinx-Gallery\n\nQuickstart\n==========\n\nSphinx-Gallery can be used to generate an example gallery from ``.py`` files,\nfor a library,\nas well as a stand-alone web page showcasing examples of a particular\nPython package, module, or class.\n\nLet's get started with a simple example or check out the\n `documentation`_ for introductions on how\n to use it and more...\n\nInstall via ``pip``\n-------------------\n\n.. installation-begin-content\n\nYou can do a direct install via ``pip`` by using:\n\n.. code-block:: bash\n\n    $ pip install sphinx-gallery\n\n.. tip::\n    Sphinx-Gallery also has support for scraping images from Matplotlib\n    and Matplotlib-based packages such as Seaborn.\n    We recommend installing system ``optipng`` binaries to reduce\n    the file sizes of the generated PNG files.\n\n.. installation-end-content\n\nAdd examples to your docs\n-------------------------\n\nLet's assume simple scenario, you have a Python package with a directory structure like this:\n\n.. code-block::\n\n    ├── doc\n    │   ├── conf.py\n    │   ├── index.rst\n    |   ├── make.bat\n    │   └── Makefile\n    ├── my_python_module\n    │   ├── __init__.py\n    │   └── mod.py\n    └── examples\n        ├── plot_example.py\n        └── README.txt (or .rst)\n\nEnable Sphinx-Gallery by adding the following to your ``doc/conf.py``:\n\n.. code-block:: python\n\n    extensions = [\n        ...\n        'sphinx_gallery.gen_gallery',\n    ]\n\n    # path to the examples scripts\n    sphinx_gallery_conf = {\n        'examples_dirs': '../examples',   # path to your example scripts\n        'gallery_dirs': 'auto_examples',  # path to where to save gallery generated output\n    }\n\nFinally just compile your docs as usual.\nSphinx-Gallery will generate reST files, adding execution outputs, and save them in ``auto_examples/``.\nAdd a link to ``auto_examples/index.rst`` to include the gallery in your documentation.\n\nWho uses Sphinx-Gallery\n=======================\n\nAn incomplete list:\n\n.. projects_list_start\n\n* `Apache TVM <https://tvm.apache.org/docs/tutorial/index.html>`_\n* `Atomistic Cookbook <https://atomistic-cookbook.org>`_\n* `auto-sklearn <https://automl.github.io/auto-sklearn/master/examples/index.html>`_\n* `Biotite <https://www.biotite-python.org/latest/examples/index.html>`_\n* `Cartopy <https://cartopy.readthedocs.io/stable/gallery/index.html>`_\n* `FURY <https://fury.gl/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `pyGIMLi <https://www.pygimli.org/_examples_auto/index.html>`_\n* `HyperSpy <https://hyperspy.org/hyperspy-doc/current/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `kikuchipy <https://kikuchipy.org/en/stable/examples/index.html>`_\n* `Matplotlib <https://matplotlib.org/stable/gallery/index>`_\n* `MNE-Python <https://mne.tools/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `napari <https://napari.org/stable/gallery.html>`_\n* `Nestle <http://kylebarbary.com/nestle/examples/index.html>`_\n* `NetworkX <https://networkx.org/documentation/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `Neuraxle <https://www.neuraxle.org/stable/examples/index.html>`_\n* `Nilearn <https://nilearn.github.io/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `OpenML <https://openml.github.io/openml-python/main/examples/index.html>`_\n* `OpenTURNS <https://openturns.github.io/openturns/latest/examples/examples.html>`_\n* `Optuna <https://optuna.readthedocs.io/en/stable/tutorial/index.html>`_\n* `PlasmaPy <https://docs.plasmapy.org/en/latest/examples.html>`_\n* `POT <https://pythonot.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `PyGMT <https://www.pygmt.org/latest/gallery/index.html>`_\n* `pyRiemann <https://pyriemann.readthedocs.io/en/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `PyStruct <https://pystruct.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `PySurfer <https://pysurfer.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `PyTorch tutorials <https://pytorch.org/tutorials>`_\n* `PyVista <https://docs.pyvista.org/examples/>`_\n* `pyxem <https://www.pyxem.org/en/stable/examples/index.html>`_\n* `RADIS <https://radis.readthedocs.io/en/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `scikit-image <https://scikit-image.org/docs/dev/auto_examples/>`_\n* `scikit-learn <https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `SimPEG <https://docs.simpeg.xyz/content/examples/>`_\n* `SKADA Scikit-adaptation <https://scikit-adaptation.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `Sphinx-Gallery <https://sphinx-gallery.github.io/stable/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `SunPy <https://docs.sunpy.org/en/stable/generated/gallery/index.html>`_\n* `Tonic <https://tonic.readthedocs.io/en/latest/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `TorchDR <https://torchdr.github.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n* `TorchIO <https://torchio.readthedocs.io/auto_examples/index.html>`_\n\n.. projects_list_end\n\nContributing\n============\n\nYou can get the latest development source from our `Github repository\n<https://github.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery>`_. You need\n``setuptools`` installed in your system to install Sphinx-Gallery. For example,\nyou can do:\n\n.. code-block:: console\n\n    $ git clone https://github.com/sphinx-gallery/sphinx-gallery\n    $ cd sphinx-gallery\n    $ conda install graphviz  # if using conda, you can get graphviz this way\n    $ pip install -e .[dev]\n\n\nCheck that you are all set by running:\n\n.. code-block:: console\n\n    $ pytest sphinx_gallery\n\nHow to cite\n===========\n\n.. citation-begin-content\n\nIf you would like to cite Sphinx-Gallery you can do so using our `Zenodo\ndeposit <https://zenodo.org/record/3741780>`_.\n\n.. _documentation: https://sphinx-gallery.github.io/\n\n.. citation-end-content\n","numLines":192,"startLine":1,"totalLines":192}}}
